NAME

    Log::Simple::Color - Log messages with different color for console

VERSION

    This document describes Log::Simple::Color version 0.0.3

SYNOPSIS

        use strict;
        use warnings;
        use Log::Simple::Color;
        
        my $log = Log::Simple::Color->new;
        
        print "current log level: ", $log->level, "\n";
        $log->level('debug');
        print "current log level: ", $log->level, "\n";
        
        $log->debug("This is a debug message");
        $log->info("This is an info message");
        $log->warning("This is a warning message");
        $log->error("This is an error message");
        
        $log->color(
            mode => 'debug',
            fg   => 'yellow',
            bg   => 'blue',
            bold => 1,
            dark => 1,
        );
        
        $log->debug("you can set different color");

DESCRIPTION

    This is a simple logging module for coloring text. You can set
    foreground color or background color for your text. This module
    supports ANSI terminals and Win32 systems.

INSTALLATION

    To install this module, run the following commands:

            perl Makefile.PL
            make
            make test
            make install

INTERFACE

 new

        my $log = Log::Simple::Color->new;

 debug

        $log->debug("This is a debug message");

 info

        $log->info("This is an info message");

 warning

        $log->warning("This is a warning message");

 error

        $log->error("This is an error message");

 level

        $log->level;
        $log->level('warning');

 color

        $log->color('debug', 'blue');
        $log->color('debug', 'blue', 'yellow');
        $log->color('debug', undef, 'yellow');
        $log->color(
            mode => 'info',
            fg   => 'blue',
            bg   => 'yellow',
        );

DEPENDENCIES

      * Win32::Console - if OS is win32

      * Term::ANSIColor - if terminal supports ANSI

INCOMPATIBILITIES

    None reported.

BUGS AND LIMITATIONS

    No bugs have been reported.

    Please report any bugs or feature requests to
    bug-log-simple-color@rt.cpan.org, or through the web interface at
    http://rt.cpan.org.

